findings.evidence:
src/http/lib.rs:4739 `let content_length = self.state.content_length;`  …  4751-4755:
    if buffer.list.is_empty() && incoming_data.len() < PREALLOCATE_MAX {
        let _ = buffer.list.try_reserve_exact(incoming_data.len());
    }
    let _ = buffer.write(remainder)?;
PREALLOCATE_MAX = 1024*1024*256 (line 317). `MutableString::write` = `extend_from_slice` (src/bun_core/string/MutableString.rs:107-112). No other reserve of the body buffer on the Content-Length receive path.

findings.proposed_fix:
When the buffer is empty and `content_length` is Some, reserve `content_length.min(PREALLOCATE_MAX)` instead of `incoming_data.len()`:
    if buffer.list.is_empty() {
        let target = content_length.unwrap_or(incoming_data.len()).min(PREALLOCATE_MAX);
        let _ = buffer.list.try_reserve_exact(target);
    }
This removes all mid-download reallocs for responses with a known Content-Length (identity or compressed-accumulate paths).
